# CODEOWNERS
# Codeowners makes GitHub block PRs until all listed maintainers approve.
# This matches the repo's AuditRunner regex: /(^|\/)(.github\/|docs\/)?codeowners$/

# Default owners for all files — adjust based on privilege level in your org policy.
* Owner: @SeanHogg

# Core application code (requires higher privileges)
# Priority reviewers: agent-runtime ops and backend maintainers. At least two approvals for non-trivial changes.
/api/ Owner: @SeanHogg
/api/* Owner: @SeanHogg

# Frontend (SSR, Cloudflare Workers)
# Strategy: author must include a "peers" review section with a reviewer名单. Minimum one approval from frontend-maintain crew.
/frontend/ Owner: @SeanHogg

# Infrastructure — should require extra scrutiny and ideally an architectural review
/Dockerfile* Owner: @SeanHogg
/.github/ Owner: @SeanHogg

# Documentation — "doc-owners" needed for safety/audit compliance
/*.md Owner: @SeanHogg
/docs/ Owner: @SeanHogg

# CI pipelines — approval required for any substantial change; at least one approval from DevOps.
/.github/workflows/ Owner: @SeanHogg
/.claude/ Owner: @SeanHogg

# Security & release scripts — require two approvals; one operations, one security.
/scripts/ Owner: @SeanHogg

# Dependencies / lockfiles — no approvals needed for dependency updates when semver bump; noise mitigation in PR template.
/pnpm-lock.yaml Owner:
/package.json Owner: